  <td valign=3Dtop style=3D'padding:0in 5.75pt 0in 5.75pt'>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>As you explore the galaxy you may discover remnants =
of
  civilizations long past. These ruins are well worth investigating &#8211;=
 they
  often contain useful information that can help your empire. If you are the
  first to encounter the ruins then your empire receives these benefits.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Ruins may also reveal secret knowledge, uncovering d=
etails
  about the galaxy&#8217;s history. At the very least they can point you in=
 the
  right direction as you learn the truth about the past.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Ancient ruins bestow an important bonus to any colony
  founded at the planet: the colony gains extra development of up to 50%. T=
his
  extra bonus is in addition to the normal colony development, allowing the
  colony to develop past 100%.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Ruins are also considered to be scenic locations, an=
d thus
  will attract tourism to any colony that has them. If ruins are at an
  uninhabited planet or moon, then you can build a resort base there to all=
ow
  tourism to the ruins.</p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal>Finally, remember that you may choose not to investi=
gate
  all ruins that you encounter. Rumour has it that some ruins conceal items
  that are better left undisturbed...</p>
